  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic W-CON-01)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This synthetic package introduces W-CON-01: the decision record records outcome Accepted while several credibility factors carry no requiredLevel or achievedLevel, leaving the acceptance decision without grounding in structured factor evidence.",
