      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI must be the absolute hemolysis index directly linked to the clinical threshold; scalar surrogate QoIs are insufficient at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index is the primary QoI and is directly compared to the clinical threshold. However, the model predicts a power-law surrogate rather than a mechanistic cell-damage integral. Achieved level 3."
